*update 6/26/23: Most of you know I was in a motorcycle accident in April 2023 that caused me to miss about three months of work. Due to the rescheduling of those clients, new appointment requests will not be open again until 2024. I understand how disappointing this may be, unfortunately I am only one person trying to serve a large group of people as best I can. It would not be beneficial to me, or to current and potential clients to continually book appointments out more than 6 months at any given time. Life is unpredictable- sometimes in amazing ways and sometimes in awful ways. I sincerely appreciate everyone’s patience. 🫶🏻
If you know anyone with an upcoming appointment please let them know the situation.

Update: we finally got to see each other! Oleg has been in an ICU room and i am, of course, unable to walk. Yesterday, PT helped me learn how to get into a wheelchair so I was able to go visit him after surgery. As a reminder I have a broken right ulna as well as a compound fracture in my right lower leg. Oleg has had 16+ hours of surgery now to address breaks in his leg, hip, pelvis, arm and collarbone. As much as I can’t wait for us to be discharged, unfortunately we will not be able to stay in our apartment during recovery. It is not wheelchair accessible whatsoever. My mother has started a GoFundMe if anyone is able to contribute or share the link. (Clickable link in my bio!) it Genuinely means so much to us to have everyone’s support. We could not make it through this without our amazing friends and family. And my chin is just bruised- I didn’t grow a goatee haha (yet!👀)

Little update! I have been discharged and am staying in a hotel near the hospital. Yesterday my mom was able to wash my hair and I put on some makeup to go visit my love at the hospital. He had his 3rd surgery on Monday for his scapula and clavicle. We finally got the police report, as well as a couple pics of Oleg’s bike. @stevesilveytattoos is graciously doing a raffle for a free tattoo, all proceeds will benefit our recovery fund 🥹🫶🏻 check him out and please share our GFM link if you haven’t yet. (Link in b!0) We will both be out of work for at least 12 weeks, probably longer for Oleg as his injuries are more extensive.

I literally always get mad at my mom for pulling out the camera. Been the same way since I was a teenager 😅 but I am so glad that in the midst of this swirling shitstorm we find ourselves in, we have a few snapshots of the happy moments. Moments where we managed to make each other smile or laugh. Moments that I would have taken for granted any other time, had we not almost lost our lives in a wreck less than 2 weeks ago. My recovery is going well so far, Oleg still has one major surgery standing between him and potentially coming “home”. I miss him so so much 😞 please check out @desire_beautyservices and @stevesilveytattoos both of whom are raffling their services FOR FREE in order to add to our recovery fund. And if you haven’t shared our GFM yet (link in b!0) it would truly mean so much to us if you would. Every single dollar will help us survive the next 12 weeks, which is the minimum time we’ve been told that we cannot return to work. Thank you all so much❤️❤️❤️❤️

*TW: Incisions and Stitches* Mini-update!! I got ALL of my stitches out today and doc says I’m doing good 🙌🏼 I should be able to start walking in about 4 weeks with a walker! Oleg had his final surgery for his leg on Friday. They had to wait this long for the artery in his leg to heal (it was crushed in the accident and had to be essentially rebuilt) so he could maintain proper bloodflow for healing. We may have found a solution for him to come home soon and still receive proper care 🤞🏼🥳 don’t forget to share our GFM if you haven’t ❤️ link in bio!
Remember when I used to do tattoos? 🥲 and had never broken a bone 😂 here’s one from April 3 when I had literally no idea we’d be smacking into a truck the next day.

Fun one from a ways back, on a super cool client 😎 can’t wait to get back to it and add on to this arm! 🌞🌛 #nctattooers #tattoo #tattooideas #femaletattooartist #ladytattooers #greenvillenc #littlebeestings #ultimatetattoosupply @ultimatetattoosupply #inked #inkedmag #girlswithtattoos

Been a while since an update! 🫶🏻 Oleg is finally able to use a wheelchair, although he is about 8 weeks out from any weight bearing on his legs still it’s a HUGE win for us mobility wise (now we don’t have to pay for ambulance transport for his doc appointments)🙌🏼 I started walking with crutches yesterday! I feel like Bambi on ice but it feels good to be using my legs again. We went out for lunch today, Oleg’s first real outing since the wreck that wasn’t a doc appointment. Slow and steady improvements, a little more each day ❤️🫶🏻😊
